cURL Command:
curl -X PUT "http://localhost:5000/customer/auth/review/1?review=This%20is%20a%20great%20book!" -b /tmp/cookies.txt

Output:
{"message":"Review successfully added/updated"}

Verification - Get reviews for book 1:
curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/review/1

Output:
{"testuser":"This is a great book!"}

Testing modification of existing review:
curl -X PUT "http://localhost:5000/customer/auth/review/1?review=Updated%20review:%20Even%20better%20on%20second%20read!" -b /tmp/cookies.txt

Output:
{"message":"Review successfully added/updated"}

Verification after update:
curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/review/1

Output:
{"testuser":"Updated review: Even better on second read!"}

Testing multiple users reviewing the same book:
First, register and login as another user:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"anotheruser","password":"pass123"}'
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/customer/login -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"anotheruser","password":"pass123"}' -c /tmp/cookies2.txt

Add review from second user:
curl -X PUT "http://localhost:5000/customer/auth/review/1?review=A%20masterpiece%20of%20African%20literature!" -b /tmp/cookies2.txt

Output:
{"message":"Review successfully added/updated"}

Verification - Both reviews present:
curl -X GET http://localhost:5000/review/1

Output:
{"testuser":"Updated review: Even better on second read!","anotheruser":"A masterpiece of African literature!"}
